<title type="html"><![CDATA[Repairing Super Mario Bros. 2 (US)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3558&amp;p=26593#p26593"><![CDATA[
Logically the only replacable componants are the resistors&amp;caps, and the SRAM too. I don't think the MMC3, ROMs or CIC will break down easily anyway. You can try replace the capacitor, as they often dryes out leading problem (here I guess the problem would be no decoupling on the main power voltage). The resistors are quite likely not breaking down unless they're burned black or something. You could try replace the SRAM, but changes that it will change anything are low.<br /><br />PS : By the way if you would switch to a non-animated avatar I guess everyone would be happy. Not really a request, just a personal suggetion...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Aug 31, 2007 10:21 am</p><hr />
